text: Franz Haslberger (3 December 1914 - 17 September 1939) was a German ski jumper. He competed in the individual event at the 1936 Winter Olympics. He was killed in action during World War II. ==References== Category:1914 births Category:1939 deaths Category:German male ski jumpers Category:Olympic ski jumpers of Germany Category:Ski jumpers at the 1936 Winter Olympics Category:People from Traunstein (district) Category:German military personnel killed in World War II
